{
  "stem": "15991.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so that was the way she was communicating with us.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We always had to come to the bathroom.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I remember the water was running.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, Jews, period, had to pay millions of dollars-- millions of marks, rather.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "For the government, just because they're Jewish.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They weren't allowed to have any money.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The condition to get my father out, I believe, was that he could leave the country at that point.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That was still possible.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so I-- my mother's sister lived in England and was able to get us all, save all our lives.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Her name was Lotte Elkon, E-L-K-A-N.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 84,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She lived in London, yes, in [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 85,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She vouched for all of us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 85,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She gave us the affidavits.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 85,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And first she vouched my brother and myself so that we could come over.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 85,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was a children's transport.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 86,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was December 1938.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 86,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was the 15th of December, 1938.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 87,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, he was still interned, he was still away, incarcerated.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 88,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 89,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Nothing, none.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 90,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He never told me about it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 90,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No, he talked a little bit to my brother but never to my mother and myself about it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 90,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It must have been devastating [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] for him.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, you see, my mother decided to send us away when-- because she just didn't know what was going to happen after my father was taken by the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I think it was a very courageous move on her part and must have been tearing her heart to pieces because I know what it would feel like if I'd had to send my children away.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was 14 and my brother was 9.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 92,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not very long.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 92,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You see, the 11th of November was Kristallnacht.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 92,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were shipped away on the 15th of December.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
